UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS BR 2406
1 A RESOLUTION designating January 6th, as Breaking Free With Ally Day.
2 WHEREAS, the safety, dignity, and well-being of children and vulnerable
3 individuals are fundamental responsibilities shared by our entire community; and
4 WHEREAS, grooming, childhood sexual abuse, and human trafficking are serious
5 crimes that cause profound and lasting harm to victims, families, and communities; and
6 WHEREAS, increasing public awareness, promoting prevention education, and
7 encouraging early intervention are essential steps in protecting children and preventing
8 exploitation; and
9 WHEREAS, Breaking Free With Ally is a nonprofit organization committed to
10 raising awareness about grooming, childhood sexual abuse, and human trafficking,
11 providing education and resources, and empowering individuals and communities to
12 recognize warning signs and take action to prevent exploitation; and
13 WHEREAS, community partnerships among families, educators, faith leaders, law
14 enforcement, service providers, and nonprofit organizations are critical in strengthening
15 prevention efforts and supporting survivors; and
16 WHEREAS, designating a day to recognize and support these efforts will
17 encourage open conversations, education, prevention initiatives, and a unified
18 commitment to safeguarding children and vulnerable individuals; and
19 WHEREAS, Kentucky urges all residents to learn the signs of grooming and
20 exploitation, support prevention and awareness efforts, and work together to protect
21 children and vulnerable individuals from abuse and trafficking;
22 NOW, THEREFORE,
23 Be it resolved by the Senate of the General Assembly of the Commonwealth of
24 Kentucky:
25 Section 1. The Senate hereby designates January 6th, as Breaking Free With
26 Ally Day in the Commonwealth of Kentucky.
27 Section 2. The Clerk of the Senate is directed to transmit a copy of this
